WHAT IS THIS FILE
The certified body profile for Blackmagic Design cameras using Generation 5
Color Science (URSA Mini Pro 12K, Pocket Cinema Camera 6K/4K G2, etc.). It
contains the exact mathematical IDT, the Blackmagic RAW decoding model, the
native wide gamut color space primaries, the custom log curve parameters
(Blackmagic RAW Film log), white balance presets, ISO sensitivity ranges,
and sensor metrology data. This is the single source of truth for linearizing
Blackmagic Gen 5 footage to scene-referred ACES2065-1.

WHY IT EXISTS
Gen 5 Color Science is designed to provide accurate skin tones and realistic
color, with Blackmagic RAW retaining the full sensor data in a compressed but
linearizable format. Integrating Blackmagic footage into an ACES or GIOP
pipeline requires exact knowledge of the native gamut and the inverse log curve
embedded in Blackmagic RAW. This file provides the open, mathematical path,
eliminating the need for a Resolve-only workflow.

HOW IT WORKS
The IDT is invoked after Blackmagic RAW has been demosaiced and partially
linearized by the SDK (which decodes the compressed RAW and applies basic
corrections). The GIOP transform chain is:
  1. Inverse Blackmagic RAW Film log curve → linear wide gamut RGB.
  2. Native wide gamut to ACES2065-1 matrix (3x3, D65-to-D60 adaptation).
  3. White balance scaling (as-shot or preset).

WHERE IT IS DEPLOYED
- DaVinci Resolve (via Resolve Color Management or DCTL)
- Nuke (via Python API with Blackmagic RAW SDK)
- Baselight (BLG stack)
- Any ACES-compliant grading or compositing tool.

WHO USES IT
- L2 GIOP Engineers: implement the IDT in pipeline tools.
- L3 GIOP Colorists: verify correct linearization before grading.
- DITs and editors working with Blackmagic RAW on non-Resolve platforms.

WHAT PROBLEM IT SOLVES
Replaces the Resolve-only dependency for Blackmagic RAW linearization by
providing an auditable, platform-agnostic IDT. Ensures that Blackmagic Gen 5
footage linearized via GIOP matches the original scene light to within
10^-6 relative error, regardless of the compositing application.

